snippet.textDisplay:
The song - its arrangement, singers, musicians have all done a wonderful job here! Costumes as well, are so beautifully designed. <3 Love the song here, and the touch of Awadhi ..


But in terms of set design and overall costume/design thinking - it is VERY SIMILAR TO OTHER COKE STUDIO projects like Pasoori. 

Since this is a creative premise, and Coke Studio is known to set the stage for future artists, it has this unspoken duty of pushing boundaries and thinking out of the box. But lately, it has had very similar tunes, approaches, and rhythms. All songs have begun to sound similar. 


Back when it all started, the songs had soul and character. Amit Trivedi, Salim Suleiman, Rahman - and the likes. 

My honest suggestion in good faith would be to rethink, innovate and stand out, instead of following trends - because that is what Coke Studio has been known for and should be known for, moving forward. 

Wishing the team all the best!
